Part I - Prosper Loan Data Exploration¶

by ( Chepngeno Millicent)¶

Introduction¶

Loan is known to be the sum of money that a legal person borrows from another with cfondition that it be returned or repaid over time or at the later date and mostly it can be repaid with interest while prosper is to lend. loan services has expanded matching investors with needy borrowers in over 35 sites world-wide sometimes within 24 hours. Since 2005, when the first lending site was founded in the U.K.,the online platforms have provided billions of dollars worth of small loans to individuals and small businesses, with an expected $25bn-plus world-wide market by 2020 (Financial Times, 2014). Measurable data about loan applicants is limited, and loan lending platforms seek to expedite loan funding by facilitating the exchange of messages and images between borrowers and potential investors, who are most times from the same nation 2 . As any other business agreement, and especially because of its risky nature,peer-to-peer loan agreements can arguably constitute a good scenario where to study the impact of legal frameworks and cultural dimensions, both in terms of loan characteristics and how quickly the investor-borrower matching is accomplished. In ProperLoanData set I am to explore a sample of Prosper loan data to uncover What factors affect a loans outcome status,What affects the borrowers APR or interest rate and if there are differences between loans depending on how large the original loan amount was.

Structure of the dataset.¶

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

Main feature(s) of interest in the dataset.¶

Taking the questions I am to answer when exploring this data into consideration therefore thae main features i will use are : First question being ,What affects the borrowers APR or interest rate?

  • LoanStatus
  • EmploymentStatus
  • StatedMonthlyIncome
  • IsBorrowerHomeowner
  • IncomeRange
  • StatedMonthlyIncome
  • BorrowerAPR
  • BorrowerState
  • ProsperRating (Alpha)

Second question being,What factors affect a loans outcome status?

  • LoanOriginalAmount
  • DebtToIncomeRatio
  • IncomeVerifiable
  • Term
  • ListingCreationDate
  • ListingCategory (numeric)

Features in the dataset that support the investigation into the feature(s) of interest¶

borrower's APR and the interest rate.

.There is a negative corelationship between the term and the borrowerAPR ,the longer the term the borrower receives the the lower the borrowerAPR due to he payment of the interest rate in installments .

.There is a positive corelationship between the loanoriginalamount and the statedmonthlyincome,the higher the statedmonthlyincome the higher he loanoriginalamount due to high probablity of clearing the loan afer a given term

.There is a negative corelationship between the the borrowersAPR and statedmonthlyincome,the higher the statedmonthlyincome of the borrower the the lower the borrersAPR.

. There is a positive corellationship between the term and the loanoriginalamount,the longer the term the higher the original amount o ensure clearence of the loan balance.

. There is a negative corelationship between the loanoriginaamount and the borrowerAPR,looking into the ratio of the loanoriginalamount and the borrowerAPR annually the higher the loan the lower the borrowerAPR

Conclusions¶

1 Factors that affect the a loan's outcome¶

income range - An increase in income range leads to an an increase in the loanoriginalamount

Term - an increase in term leads to an increase in the loanoriginalamount

BorrowersAPR- an increase in the borrowersAPR leads to decrease in the loanoriginaamount

2 factors that affect the borrowersAPR¶

income range - An increase in income range leads to an an increase in the loanoriginalamount and enjoys a low borrowersAPR

Stated Monthly Income- An increase in the statedmonthlyincome leads to a decrease in the borrowersAPR
